Seven Companies Get Istanbul Bridge Tender Documents, Sabah Says

-- B y   S t e v e   B r y a n t
-- 
2011-04-06T05:17:50Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-06/seven-companies-get-istanbul-bridge-tender-documents-sabah-says.html
Seven companies have so far
requested tender documents for the construction of a third
bridge over the Bosporus Strait in Istanbul, Sabah newspaper
reported.  The total cost of the bridge, associated highway and
another bridge to be built over the Gulf of Izmit will be $11
billion or $12 billion, Sabah said, citing Cahit Turhan, head of
the Turkish roads authority.  The Bosporus bridge will carry road traffic on its upper
level, with a train line on the lower tier, the newspaper said.
 Turkey  aims to conclude the bidding this year and break ground
in 2012, the newspaper said.  Click here for web link  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
